Ekiti State Police Command on Wednesday confirmed an attack by suspected thugs on the campaign venue of the candidate of the Social Democratic Party (SDP) and former governor, Chief Segun Oni in the Efon local government area of the state. The Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), ASP Sunday Abutu noted the gun-wielding political thugs invaded the campaign ground of the former governor and made spirited efforts to disrupt it. He said, “Yes, the hoodlums came to the venue with dangerous weapons to disrupt the consultation process of the SDP candidate, Chief Segun Oni, but our men were able to put the situation under control. “The police have begun investigation and arrest will be made and those behind it will surely have a case to answer.” YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE We Have Not Had Water Supply In Months ― Abeokuta Residents In spite of the huge investment in the water sector by the government and international organisations, water scarcity has grown to become a perennial nightmare for residents of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. This report x-rays the lives and experiences of residents in getting clean, potable and affordable water amidst the surge of COVID-19 cases in the state… Selfies, video calls and Chinese documentaries: The things you’ll meet onboard Lagos-Ibadan train The Lagos-Ibadan railway was inaugurated recently for a full paid operation by the Nigerian Railway Corporation after about a year of free test-run. Our reporter joined the train to and fro Lagos from Ibadan and tells his experience in this report… [ICYMI] Lekki Shootings: Why We Lied About Our Presence — General Taiwo The Lagos State Judicial Panel of Inquiry probing the killings at Lekki Toll Gate, on Saturday resumed viewing of the 24hrs footage of the October 20, 2020 shooting of #EndSARS protesters by personnel of the Nigerian Army…